The 'next' variable is initialized as empty. Then, for each i in 0 to N-1:

if i !=0, check if current string starts with next (which is the last character of previous). Then set next to current's last character. So in Fortran:

Initialize next_char as a character variable.

Loop over all i from 1 to N:

   Loop over j from 1 to i-1:

      if s(i) == s(j), then ans = .false., exit loops. Then, check the chain: prev_char = last character of s(1)

Loop i from 2 to N:

   if s(i)(1:1) /= prev_char, then ans = .false., exit. prev_char = last character of s(i)
